Write a program to find the maximum odd number present in an array.

Input Format:
Input consists of 'n+1' integers where n is the number of elements in the array. The first integer input is 'n' and the next 'n' integers .
correspond to the elements in the array, Assume that the elements to be stored in the array should be positive integers.

Output Format:
Output consists of a single integer which corresponds to the maximum odd number.
Sample Input 1:
5
9
11
15
20
22

Sample Output 1:
15

solution:
import java.util.*;
public class Main
{
  public static void main(String[] args) {
  Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
  int n=sc.nextInt();
  int []arr= new int[n];
  for(int i=0;i<arr.length; i++){
  arr[i]=sc.nextInt();
}
  int max=arr[0];
  for(int i = 0 ;i<arr.length;i++){
  if(arr[i]%2!= 0 && arr[i]>max){
  max=arr[i];
}
System.out.print(max);
sc.close();
}
}
